Glyptapanteles clanisae

is compared with the original description of 

G. spodopterae

and it resembles in having a row of long hairs on basal half of hind wing but differs in having a weakly concave margin of vannal lobe (margin of vannal lobe smooth and convex in 

G. spodopterae

); mid femur entirely yellow (mid femur entirely black in 

G. spodopterae

); and first metasomal tergum with deep dorsal concavity having fine transverse striations basally and shallow sculpture apically (first metasomal tergum smooth and shiny in 

G. spodopterae

).
